subSubSection.paragraph:
Legs. Subcoxa I with 5 chaetae on a row and 2 psp; subcoxa II with an anterior row of 9 chaetae, posterior row of 4 chaetae, 2 extra chaetae near p row and 6 psp; subcoxa III with one row of 9 chaetae and 2 posterior psp (
Figs 37
A–C). Trochanteral organ with about 23 spine-like chaetae (
Fig. 37D
). Tibiotarsus not subdivided, outer side with 3 proximal larger ciliated chaetae apically acuminate (
e
), inner side with 9 mac weakly ciliated (
ai
and 
pi
), and anterior side with 2 mac (
ae
) on proximal half (
Fig. 37E
). Unguis with 4 inner teeth, b.t. subequal to m.t. in length, a.t. smaller. Unguiculus with all lamellae smooth and acuminate, except 
pe
serrated and with a small proximal tooth; ratio unguis: unguiculus = 1: 0.57. Tibiotarsal smooth chaeta 1.08 larger than unguiculus and tenent hair 0.90 smaller than unguis outer edge (
Fig. 37F
).

Collophore. Anterior side with 14 chaetae, 7 proximal spine-like chaetae, 1 ciliated chaeta, 4 ciliated chaetae apically acuminate and 2 mac distally; posterior side with 5 chaetae, 4 thin ciliated chaetae widely distributed and 1 smooth chaeta distally; lateral flap with about 19 chaetae, 5 smooth and 14 ciliated (
Fig. 38A
).

